"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92152","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-10-14","<p><strong>The table sets out the number of employees, within each performance category, who have declared a disability. </strong><strong>The Department for Culture, Media and Sport (DCMS) takes seriously its obligations to collect diversity data as required by the Equality Act 2010. All staff have been asked to provide personal diversity data to be held anonymously, and we continue to encourage increased declaration by staff. As such these figures will not be fully representative of workforce diversity</strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>i) </strong><strong>Disability</strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>DCMS</p></td><td><p>EYR Rating</p></td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Disability</p></td><td><p><strong>Exceptional</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Good</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Must Improve</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Not disclosed</p></td><td><p>31</p></td><td><p>64</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>No</p></td><td><p>52</p></td><td><p>76</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Prefer not to say</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Yes</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>*The disclosure of numbers where they amount to fewer than five could enable identification of individuals to whom this information relates. This would amount to a release of their personal data in breach of the Data Protection Act</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>ii)&amp;iii) Full –time/part –time </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong>The following table sets out the number of employees, within each performance category, who work full time or part time.</strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>DCMS</p></td><td><p>EYR Rating</p></td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Part time full time</p></td><td><p><strong>Exceptional</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Good</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Must Improve</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Full Time</p></td><td><p>79</p></td><td><p>138</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Part Time</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>*The disclosure of numbers where they amount to fewer than five could enable identification of individuals to whom this information relates. This would amount to a release of their personal data in breach of the Data Protection Act</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-10-14T16:30:56.616752Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92152/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92152/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92152/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-09-26","Performance Appraisal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many officials in his Department who received the (a) exceeded, (b) met and (c) must improve performance mark under the Civil Service Employment Policy Performance Management System (i) had a disability, (ii) worked full-time and (iii) worked part-time in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","209624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92153","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-10-14","<p><strong>The table sets out the number of employees who completed the Civil Service Employment Policy Performance Management System in 2013-14; and the proportion of those officials who received the (a) exceeded, (b) met and (c) must improve performance mark. and how many and what proportion who (i) did and (ii) did not qualify for a bonus.</strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>DCMS</p></td><td><p>EYR Rating</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>Exceptional</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Good</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Must Improve</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Grand Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>87</p></td><td><p>148</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>240</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Percentage</p></td><td><p>36%</p></td><td><p>62%</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td><td><p>100%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Bonus</p></td><td><p><strong>Eligible</strong></p></td><td><p><strong> Not eligible</strong></p></td><td><p><strong> Grand Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p>36%</p></td><td><p>64%</p></td><td><p>100%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-10-14T16:32:29.9147223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92153/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92153/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92153/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-09-26","Performance Appraisal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many officials in his Department completed the Civil Service Employment Policy Performance Management System in 2013-14; how many and what proportion of those officials received the (a) exceeded, (b) met and (c) must improve performance mark; and how many and what proportion (i) did and (ii) did not qualify for a bonus under that process.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","209646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92154","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-10-14","<p>Ongoing work with TNA is allowing the Department to develop a plan to assess the volume of work in this area and the resource needed for DCMS to meet it’s commitments. We would expect to be in a position to set out targets in time for the May 2015 Record Transfer Report.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-10-14T16:31:14.3564129Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92154/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92154/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92154/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-09-26","Public Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what targets have been set for the release of his Department's material to the National Archives; what progress has been made in meeting those targets; and how many staff in his Department are engaged in reviewing records for that purpose.","false","Biography information for Lord Beith","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Sir Alan Beith","209607"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92155","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-10-14","<p><strong>The table sets out the number of employees within each performance category for the 2013-14 reporting year for assessments received to date by gender, ethnicity and age. </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong>a) </strong><strong>Gender</strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>DCMS</p></td><td><p>EYR Rating</p></td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Gender</p></td><td><p><strong>Exceptional</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Good</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Must Improve</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Female</p></td><td><p>45</p></td><td><p>62</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Male</p></td><td><p>42</p></td><td><p>86</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Grand Total</p></td><td><p>87</p></td><td><p>148</p></td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>*The disclosure of numbers where they amount to fewer than five could enable identification of individuals to whom this information relates. This would amount to a release of their personal data in breach of the Data Protection Act</p><p> </p><p><strong>b) </strong><strong>Ethnicity</strong></p><p>The Department for Culture, Media and Sport (DCMS) takes seriously its obligations to collect diversity data as required by the Equality Act 2010. All staff have been asked to provide personal diversity data to be held anonymously, and we continue to encourage increased declaration by staff. As such these figures will not be fully representative of workforce diversity</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>DCMS</p></td><td><p>EYR Rating</p></td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Ethnicity</p></td><td><p><strong>Exceptional</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Good</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Must Improve</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Not disclosed</p></td><td><p>35</p></td><td><p>64</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Any Other Ethnic Background</p></td><td> </td><td><p>*</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Asian - Indian</p></td><td> </td><td><p>*</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Asian - Pakistani</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Black - African</p></td><td> </td><td><p>*</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Black - Caribbean</p></td><td> </td><td><p>*</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Black - Other</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Mixed - Black Caribbean &amp; White</p></td><td> </td><td><p>*</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Mixed - Other</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Prefer not to say</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>White</p></td><td><p>48</p></td><td><p>69</p></td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>*The disclosure of numbers where they amount to fewer than five could enable identification of individuals to whom this information relates. This would amount to a release of their personal data in breach of the Data Protection Act</p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>c) </strong><strong>Age</strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>DCMS</p></td><td><p>EYR Rating</p></td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Age</p></td><td><p><strong>Exceptional</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Good</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Must Improve</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>16-24</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>25-29</p></td><td><p>16</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>30-34</p></td><td><p>14</p></td><td><p>21</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>35-39</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>30</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>40-44</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>16</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>45-49</p></td><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>50-54</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>23</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>55-59</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>13</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>60-64</p></td><td><p>*</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>65+</p></td><td> </td><td><p>*</p></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>*The disclosure of numbers where they amount to fewer than five could enable identification of individuals to whom this information relates. This would amount to a release of their personal data in breach of the Data Protection Act</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-10-14T16:32:47.9849232Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92155/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92155/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92155/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-09-26","Performance Appraisal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many officials in his Department of each (a) gender, (b) ethnicity and (c) age received the Civil Service Employment Policy Performance Management System's (i) exceeded, (ii) met and (iii) must improve performance mark in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","209476"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92156","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-10-14","<p>The Government has introduced a new system of independent self-regulation of the press that protects press freedom whilst offering real redress when mistakes are made. This is a matter for independent press self-regulators. The Government has no plans formally to review the law in this particular area.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-10-14T16:31:49.3212712Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92156/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92156/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92156/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-09-26","Children: Privacy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps his Department plans to take to ensure that newspapers only publish photographs of children when they have parental consent to do so.","false","Biography information for Oliver Colvile","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Oliver Colvile","209781"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92157","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-18","<p>Around 600 UK Armed Forces personnel are currently deployed on operations in Afghanistan and around a further 2,930 are deployed on operations in other countries. Information on the stationed location of all UK Regular Forces is available at <a title="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/376061/QLS_Quarterly_Location_Statistics__October_2014.pdf#page=4" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/376061/QLS_Quarterly_Location_Statistics__October_2014.pdf#page=4" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/376061/QLS_Quarterly_Location_Statistics__October_2014.pdf#page=4</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>Notes:</strong></p><ol type="1"><li>‘UK Armed Forces personnel’ includes UK Regular Forces, Gurkhas, Full Time Reserve Service personnel and mobilised reservists.</li><li>‘Other countries’ excludes deployments in the UK, Afghanistan and personnel on board Naval Vessels.</li><li>Data for personnel deployed on operations only includes personnel who are deployed to an overseas location with an assigned country code. Personnel on overseas training exercises are excluded.</li></ol><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-12-18T16:31:20.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92157/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92157/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92157/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92157/answer/previousversion/22766","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many British service personnel are serving in (a) Afghanistan and (b) other countries.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","209788"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92158","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-17","<p>The 2014 Amendment to the Agreement between the Government of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland and the Government of the United States of America for Cooperation on the Uses of Atomic Energy for Mutual Defense Purposes 1958, otherwise known as the Amendment Agreement to the 1958 UK-US Mutual Defence Agreement (MDA), has been laid before Parliament in accordance with the Constitutional Reform and Governance Act 2010. This Amendment Agreement is intended to renew and update certain provisions in the MDA to ensure their continuing relevance and validity for a further period of 10 years until 31 December 2024. The original MDA and its subsequent amendments are available in the libraries, as they were previously laid under the Ponsonby Rule. In line with long-established practice, and as accepted by Parliament during the 2004 renewal, the annexes of the MDA cannot be placed in the libraries because of the sensitivity of their contents.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-10-17T11:44:39.6529686Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92158/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92158/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92158/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-26","USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will place in the Library a copy of (a) the current text of the 1958 UK-US Mutual Defence Agreement and its annexes, as subsequently amended since the Agreement originally entered into force and (b) any amendments to the Agreement and its annexes that the Government proposes for when they are renewed.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","209761"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92159","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-16","<p>HMS Defender deployed in June 2014 and is part of a multinational operation to provide maritime security to the Gulf region. She is currently part of an integrated carrier strike group protecting the USS George H W Bush.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-16T15:01:45.3571645Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92159/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92159/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92159/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","HMS Defender","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the current mission tasking is for HMS Defender; and how long she has been assigned to this task.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","209756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92160","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-29","<p>I am withholding the information as its disclosure would or would be likely to prejudice relations between the United Kingdom and another State.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-29T17:28:07.013183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92160/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92160/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92160/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92160/answer/previousversion/22764","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Qatar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what UK armed forces assets and personnel are currently based at al-Udeid.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","209757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92161","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-15","<p>The total spent on studies to inform the decision on whether to refurbish or replace the existing warhead during the period until 30 September 2014 comprises £72.9 million on technology studies to support refurbishment of the current system and explore options for a potential future warhead; and £4.6 million on studies to support the decision whether to refurbish or replace the existing warhead.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-10-15T15:09:26.2548714Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92161/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92161/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92161/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Trident","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Answer of 14 January 2013, Official Report, column 601W, on Trident, how much his Department has spent to date on studies of whether to refurbish or replace the existing Trident warhead design.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","209770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92162","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-14","<p>I am withholding the information requested as its disclosure would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-14T15:12:56.6835409Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92162/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92162/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92162/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Tornado Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the maximum daily sortie rate is for six Tornado fast jets configured for ground attack missions.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","209758"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92163","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-17","<p>The UK currently has eight Tornado GR4 aircraft assigned to strike operations in Iraq. As of 8 October, there were 133 personnel deployed to RAF Akrotiri in Cyprus to support these missions.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-17T13:35:15.8559564Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92163/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92163/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92163/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Islamic State","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what UK armed forces (a) assets and (b) personnel will be used in attacking ISIL targets in Iraq.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","209771"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92164","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-17","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer my hon. Friend the Member for Mid Worcestershire (Mr Luff) gave on 25 June 2012 (Official Report, column 5) to the right hon. Member for South West Norfolk (Elizabeth Truss). <br><br>My hon. Friend the Minister of State for the Armed Forces (The Rt Hon Mark Francois) also wrote to the hon. Member on 2 October 2014 (reference MSU-04-04-02-21) in respect of plans for Tornado GR4.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-10-17T13:20:07.8909571Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92164/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92164/answer","Hansard Extract 25 June 2012..doc ; 20141002 RAF typhoon squadron at RAF Lossiemouth MSU4 4 2 21 Min(AF) to Angus Robertson MP 001.pdf","Hansard Extract 25 June 2012..doc ; 20141002 RAF typhoon squadron at RAF Lossiemouth MSU4 4 2 21 Min(AF) to Angus Robertson MP 001.pdf","Military Aircraft ; letter dated 2 October","Military Aircraft ; letter dated 2 October","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92164/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Tornado Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when the planned out-of-service date is for Tornado fast jets.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","209759"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92165","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-20","<p>The UK has a small Defence section working in the British Embassy in Baghdad. This permanent presence is currently supplemented by around 20 personnel acting in support of operations against ISIL terrorists. These personnel are performing a range of roles including: supporting humanitarian operations, providing training to Kurdish forces and supporting coalition planning activities. The UK currently has no major military assets based in Iraq.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-20T16:18:50.1917603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92165/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92165/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92165/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92165/answer/previousversion/22756","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Iraq","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what UK armed forces assets and personnel are stationed in Iraq.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","209772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92166","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-12-17","<p>UK personnel in Iraq perform a number of roles. This includes supporting UK and coalition airstrikes against ISIL in Iraq. Iraqi security forces are able to communicate with coalition aircraft through coalition HQs including the Iraqi Joint Operating Centre in Baghdad. Coalition aircraft in Iraq either engage in dynamic targeting, for example responding to Iraqi forces under fire, or in deliberate targeting, when for example attacking previously identified ISIL positions prior to an advance by Iraqi security forces.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-12-17T17:36:36.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92166/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92166/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92166/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92166/answer/previousversion/22755","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Iraq","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether forward air controllers are directing airstrikes in Iraq.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","209773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92167","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-16","<p>As the UK has no sovereignty rights within the Arctic our role in regional security is delivered through our active membership of the various multilateral fora which contribute to underpinning security within the Arctic region. Furthermore, the UK is a long standing observer to the Arctic Council and is one of only four sub-Arctic nations invited to take part in the Arctic Security Forces Roundtable (ASFR). The Government, including the Ministry of Defence, holds a number of security interests in the region in high regard (Freedom of Navigation, Maritime security, energy security) and we use our global influence and ASFR membership to promote compliance with international law and norms.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-16T15:07:02.2909563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92167/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92167/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92167/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Arctic","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the UK's role is in Arctic security; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","209767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92168","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-14","<p>As has been the practice of successive Governments, we do not comment on intelligence matters.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-14T15:12:23.1653475Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92168/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92168/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92168/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether targeting intelligence gathered by (a) Rivet Joint and (b) ISTAR assets has been provided to allies for targets within Syria.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","209755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92169","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-21","<p>The 1958 UK-US Mutual Defence Agreement is a bilateral treaty which provides the basis of the UK’s relationship with the US in respect of nuclear propulsion and nuclear warheads. <br><br>Most of the activity carried out under the treaty comprises exchanging information, which takes place through a series of joint working groups. <br><br>In addition, there are two enhanced collaborations, which are focused on developing capabilities:<br><br>Enhanced Nuclear Safety – the objective of which is to develop architectures and technologies related to warhead safety.<br><br>Warhead Electrical System – the objective of which is to develop architectures and technologies related to warhead electrical systems.<br><br>Both enhanced collaborations contribute to ensuring that the UK maintains our nuclear warhead stockpile on a continuing basis.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-10-21T16:11:25.7033914Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92169/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92169/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92169/answer","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92169/answer/previousversion/22735","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the titles and objectives are of all enhanced collaborations under way under the auspices of the UK-US Mutual Defence Agreement.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","209762"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92170","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-15","<p>I am withholding information about vacant Ministry of Defence Police posts at the Atomic Weapons Establishment, Burghfield, for the purposes of safeguarding national security.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-15T15:05:50.1142184Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92170/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92170/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92170/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Ministry of Defence Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of posts at the Ministry of Defence Police complement at the Atomic Weapons Establishment, Burghfield, are currently vacant.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","209763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92171","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-15","<p>The Ministry of Defence has issued five Invitations To Negotiate in relation to the granting of a concession for Marchwood Sea Mounting Centre. However, in keeping with previous practice, I have concluded that at this stage the interests of the transaction are best served by keeping confidential the identity of those participating parties.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-10-15T16:53:41.8154502Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92171/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92171/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92171/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Marchwood Military Port","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many of the organisations interested in leasing the Sea Monitoring Centre site at Marchwood in New Forest East constituency have been issued with his Department's invitation to negotiate; and what his policy is on the circumstances under which issues of commercial confidentiality inhibit revealing information.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","209791"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92172","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-16","<p>The Misconduct process in respect of allegations that a number of Ministry of Defence Police (MDP) officers failed to complete their duties correctly at the Atomic Weapons Establishment Burghfield continues. Any immediate issues of concern identified have now been addressed by the MDP and further matters picked up during the ongoing disciplinary process will be actioned. A report will be prepared by the Chief Constable when the disciplinary process has completed.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-16T15:03:51.5391111Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92172/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92172/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92172/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","AWE Burghfield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 22 January 2014, Official Report, column 222W, on the Atomic Weapons Establishment, what the conclusions and recommendations are of the investigation into shortfalls in policing standards and neglect of duties at the Atomic Weapons Establishment, Burghfield; and if he will place in the Library a copy of the report of the investigation.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","209764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92173","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-16","<p>No single Ministry of Defence official works exclusively on Arctic issues, but defence advice is provided as necessary to the Foreign and Commonwealth Office which leads on the UK’s approach to them.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-16T15:07:57.8292713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92173/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92173/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92173/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Arctic","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many officials in his Department work exclusively on Arctic issues; and what the (a) title of position and (b) grade is of each such official.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","209765"
