"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92175","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-15","<p>The costs for Operation PATWIN were borne by the Department for International Development.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-15T15:15:04.9927201Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92175/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92175/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92175/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Philippines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost was to his Department of Operation Patwin, by (a) humanitarian supplies delivered by ship, (b) non-physical humanitarian support and (c) all other costs.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Gavin Shuker","209714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92176","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-15","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) has set a target of preparing 10,000 records for transfer to The National Archives in the period 1 April 2014 – 31 March 2015. As at 1 October 2014 the MOD has prepared over 5,000 records, and is on course to achieve 10,000 by 31 March 2015. There are 14 Departmental staff engaged in the review, selection and release of MOD records to The National Archives.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-15T15:03:54.3737464Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92176/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92176/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92176/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Public Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what targets have been set for the release of his Department's material to the National Archives; what progress has been made in meeting those targets; and how many staff in his Department are engaged in reviewing records for that purpose.","false","Biography information for Lord Beith","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Sir Alan Beith","209608"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92177","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-21","<p>41,130 Ministry of Defence (MOD) civilian personnel below the Senior Civil Service were the subject of a Performance Appraisal Report (PAR) for reporting year 2013-14 and therefore took part in Performance Management.</p><p> </p><p>The moderated performance outcomes are as follows:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p>Box 1</p></td><td><p>Box 2</p></td><td><p>Box 3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Submitted PARs:</p></td><td><p>9,690</p></td><td><p>28,940</p></td><td><p>2,510</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Proportion:</p></td><td><p>23.5%</p></td><td><p>70.4%</p></td><td><p>6.1%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>A non-consolidated performance award has been made to those individuals who received a Box 1 outcome.</p><p> </p><p>The MOD will publish an annual report on the outcome of the performance management process later this year; this will include a thorough analysis of the 2013-14 data broken down by declared protected characteristics. It will also show the relevant declaration rates in support of this data analysis.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","209625 ; 209647","2014-10-21T16:38:58.4632383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92177/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92177/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92177/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92177/answer/previousversion/22788","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Performance Appraisal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many officials in his Department of each (a) gender, (b) ethnicity and (c) age received the Civil Service Employment Policy Performance Management System's (i) exceeded, (ii) met and (iii) must improve performance mark in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","209477"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92178","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-16","<p>There have been 12 Service Complaints recorded on the Joint Personnel Administration Service and submitted to Commanding Officers of Royal Naval Reserve Units in the last three years. <br><br>It is not possible to determine how much time has been spent investigating each case; investigations can be conducted at any phase of the Service Complaint management process, and some of these cases are ongoing.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-16T16:07:24.0799711Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92178/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92178/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92178/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Reserve Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Service Complaints have been made in the Royal Navy Reserve in the last three years; and how long it has taken to investigate each case.","false","Biography information for Mr Charles Kennedy","Ross, Skye and Lochaber","Mr Charles Kennedy","209553"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92179","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-21","<p>41,130 Ministry of Defence (MOD) civilian personnel below the Senior Civil Service were the subject of a Performance Appraisal Report (PAR) for reporting year 2013-14 and therefore took part in Performance Management.</p><p> </p><p>The moderated performance outcomes are as follows:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p>Box 1</p></td><td><p>Box 2</p></td><td><p>Box 3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Submitted PARs:</p></td><td><p>9,690</p></td><td><p>28,940</p></td><td><p>2,510</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Proportion:</p></td><td><p>23.5%</p></td><td><p>70.4%</p></td><td><p>6.1%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>A non-consolidated performance award has been made to those individuals who received a Box 1 outcome.</p><p> </p><p>The MOD will publish an annual report on the outcome of the performance management process later this year; this will include a thorough analysis of the 2013-14 data broken down by declared protected characteristics. It will also show the relevant declaration rates in support of this data analysis.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","209477 ; 209625","2014-10-21T16:38:58.9006528Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92179/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92179/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92179/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92179/answer/previousversion/22787","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-26","Performance Appraisal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many officials in his Department completed the Civil Service Employment Policy Performance Management System in 2013-14; how many and what proportion of those officials received the (a) exceeded, (b) met and (c) must improve performance mark; and how many and what proportion (i) did and (ii) d