"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92238","Department of Health","false","2014-10-17","<p>The Department implemented the Civil Service Performance Management Policy on 1 April 2013 for Administration Officer to Grade 6 staff. On 31 March the end of the first year of implementation was reached.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The overall distribution for the 2013-14 Performance Management year was:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Exceeded 440 (24%)</p><p> </p><p>Met 1271 (73%)</p><p> </p><p>Improvement needed 46 (3%)</p><p> </p><p>Total 1663</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>A non-consolidated performance related award was made to those in the “Exceeded” category.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-10-17T10:04:57.9989717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92238/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92238/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92238/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-26","Performance Appraisal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many officials in his Department completed the Civil Service Employment Policy Performance Management System in 2013-14; how many and what proportion of those officials received the (a) exceeded, (b) met and (c) must improve performance mark; and how many and what proportion (i) did and (ii) did not qualify for a bonus under that process.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","209653"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92239","Department of Health","false","2014-10-15","<p>NHS England is currently reviewing its programme of patient experience and outcomes data collection. The insight review aims to ensure that the data collected meets the needs of NHS England and its partners as effectively as possible. To inform this review, a steering group has been meeting quarterly to discuss priorities for data collection. This group includes a number of national stakeholder organisations in the health and care system; clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) and NHS trusts; the third sector and patient groups; and clinical representatives. The review is also being informed by interviews with patient experience data leads in CCGs and commissioning support units. A new insight strategy will be published by NHS England in spring 2015.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","209665 ; 209709","2014-10-15T15:35:43.870443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92239/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92239/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92239/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-26","HIV Infection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether the development of a patient experience survey for HIV has been considered as part of NHS England's review of patient experience.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","209664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92240","Department of Health","false","2014-10-15","<p>NHS England is currently reviewing its programme of patient experience and outcomes data collection. The insight review aims to ensure that the data collected meets the needs of NHS England and its partners as effectively as possible. To inform this review, a steering group has been meeting quarterly to discuss priorities for data collection. This group includes a number of national stakeholder organisations in the health and care system; clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) and NHS trusts; the third sector and patient groups; and clinical representatives. The review is also being informed by interviews with patient experience data leads in CCGs and commissioning support units. A new insight strategy will be published by NHS England in spring 2015.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","209664 ; 209709","2014-10-15T15:35:43.7729928Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92240/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92240/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92240/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-26","Patients: Surveys","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the timetable is for publishing the outcomes of NHS England's review of patient experience.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","209665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92241","Department of Health","false","2014-10-17","<p>Public Health England (PHE) has worked closely with the National Travel Health Network and Centre (NaTHNaC) to raise awareness of Middle East Respiratory Syndrome Coronavirus (MERS-CoV). There is detailed information and advice for travellers on how to protect themselves from infection, and how to access medical care if they feel unwell on their return to the United Kingdom. This advice can be accessed via the NaTHNaC and PHE websites.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Additionally PHE has developed posters providing travel advice to raise awareness of MERS-CoV and provide advice on how to reduce the risk of infection. These posters are available on the PHE website and have also been distributed through PHE social network platforms, and shared with airports and air carriers. There is also specific advice provided for people attending the Hajj.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>PHE has worked with national, local and ethnic media to raise awareness of MERS-CoV with press releases, social media activity, and provision of expert spokespeople. This has been both proactive, emphasising travel advice for travellers to the Middle East, and also reactive – providing information and clarification about public safety following imported cases of MERS-CoV in the UK.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-10-17T13:29:35.1646867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92241/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92241/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92241/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-26","Viral Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department has taken to raise awareness of the Middle East Respiratory Syndrome coronavirus.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","209666"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92242","Department of Health","false","2014-10-15","<p>Since the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) issued its supplementary advice to its appraisal committees on the appraisal of life extending, end-of-life treatments in January 2009, NICE has not published final technology appraisal guidance on any treatments for advanced pancreatic cancer.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>NICE is currently developing technology appraisal guidance on two treatments for pancreatic cancer:</p><p> </p><p>- Abraxane (paclitaxel) in combination with gemcitabine for treating previously untreated metastatic adenocarcinoma of the pancreas (final guidance is expected in January 2015); and</p><p> </p><p>- Theraloc (nimotuzumab) for the first line treatment of metastatic pancreatic cancer (final guidance is expected in August 2015).</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2014-10-15T15:33:22.2823668Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92242/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92242/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92242/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-26","Pancreatic Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will assess the effect of the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence's three-month end-of-life threshold on the number of treatments for advanced pancreatic cancer.","false","Biography information for Ian Swales","Redcar","Ian Swales","209582"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92243","Department of Health","false","2014-10-17","<p>The Department has two full-time reviewers, supported by a team leader. The Department is recruiting two additional full-time staff as sensitivity reviewers to support the transfer of records to The National Archives.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Departmental progress is reported to The National Archives on a bi-annual basis and is available on their website at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/about/record-transfer-report.htm" target="_blank">http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/about/record-transfer-report.htm</a></p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-10-17T13:23:55.4194181Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92243/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92243/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92243/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-26","Public Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what targets have been set for the release of his Department's material to the National Archives; what progress has been made in meeting those targets; and how many staff in his Department are engaged in reviewing records for that purpose.","false","Biography information for Lord Beith","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Sir Alan Beith","209611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92244","Department of Health","false","2014-10-20","<p>Since 1 April, NHS England has been responsible for securing high quality outcomes for patients with haematological conditions. It has published a number of service specifications for specialised haematological conditions, both for adults and children, which set out what providers should have in place to deliver evidence-based, safe and effective services. These specifications aim to ensure equity of access to a nationally consistent, high quality service for patients.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Clinical commissioning groups are responsible for provision of non-specialist haematology services locally. Local commissioners work closely with providers to consider the most appropriate clinical model for the delivery of haematology services.</p><p> </p><p><br> <br></p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-10-20T17:52:27.668012Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92244/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92244/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92244/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-26","Haematology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent assessment he has made of the level of demand for haematology services in (a) England and (b) the North East of England; and what steps he is taking to ensure that resources are able to meet demand.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","209775"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92245","Department of Health","false","2014-10-17","<p>This is a matter for the National Health Service locally.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We have written to Paul Garvin, Chair of the North Tees and Hartlepool NHS Foundation Trust, informing him of the hon. Member’s enquiry. He will reply shortly and a copy of the letter will be placed in the Library.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-10-17T12:22:21.3548589Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92245/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92245/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92245/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-26","North Tees and Hartlepool NHS Foundation Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will take steps to ensure that the haematology department at North Tees and Hartlepool NHS Foundation Trust is retained and that vacancies at that trust are filled; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","209785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92246","Department of Health","false","2014-10-15","<p>The location and number of fast food takeaways is a matter for each local planning authority to determine under their local plans. The Health and Wellbeing Planning Practice Guidance states that promoting access to healthy food is one of the issues that could be considered when making planning decisions.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In March 2014, Public Health England issued a briefing “Obesity and the environment: regulating the growth of fast food outlets” which addresses the opportunities to limit the number of fast food outlets, especially near schools, and gives practical advice to local planners and public health professionals. This briefing has been attached.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-10-15T16:04:38.4715274Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92246/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92246/answer","PHE Obesity and environment March2014.pdf","PHE Obesity and environment March2014.pdf","Obesity and the Environment March 2014","Obesity and the Environment March 2014","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92246/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-26","Fast Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to address the problem of obesity arising from the over-concentration of hot-food outlets.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","209784"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92247","Department of Health","false","2014-10-17","<p>The most recent National Health Service annual workforce census was published by the Health and Social Care Information Centre (HSCIC) in March 2014 and shows that in September 2013 there were 1,507 doctors with a specialty of haematology working in England; this represents a 13% increase since September 2010.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The number of full-time equivalent doctors with a specialty of haematology working in the NHS in England and the North East as at 30 September in 2010 and 2013 is shown in the attached table.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The next NHS annual workforce census reflecting the position as at 30 September 2014 will be published by the HSCIC in March 2015.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-10-17T10:18:59.2850792Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92247/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92247/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92247/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-26","Haematology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of haematology specialists working in (a) England and (b) the North East; and how that number has changed since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","209782"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92248","Department of Health","false","2014-10-15","<p>The location and number of fast food takeaways is a matter for each local planning authority to determine under their local plans. The Health and Wellbeing Planning Practice Guidance states that promoting access to healthy food is one of the issues that could be considered when making planning decisions.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In March 2014, Public Health England issued a briefing “Obesity and the environment: regulating the growth of fast food outlets” which addresses the opportunities to limit the number of fast food outlets, especially near schools, and gives practical advice to local planners and public health professionals. This briefing has been attached.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-10-15T15:59:14.4820104Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92248/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92248/answer","PHE Obesity and environment March2014.pdf","PHE Obesity and environment March2014.pdf","Obesity and the Environment March 2014","Obesity and the Environment March 2014","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92248/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-26","Fast Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to address the problem of fast food takeaways near schools having a damaging effect on the health of children.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","209805"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92249","Department of Health","false","2014-10-17","<p>The number of vacant and unfilled posts for haematology specialists working in England and the North East is not collected by the Department.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-10-17T09:06:33.1510593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92249/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92249/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92249/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-26","Haematology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of vacant and unfilled posts for haematology specialists working in (a) England and (b) the North East.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","209780"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92250","Department of Health","false","2014-10-23","<p>Public Health England (PHE) works closely with all the agencies responsible for supporting travellers at the United Kingdom’s borders, including airline operators, Port Health officials and the UK Border Force.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Established and well-tested procedures are in place to ensure that any traveller exhibiting illness during travel can be assessed and given appropriate care.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In view of the current Ebola outbreak in West Africa PHE issued additional specific guidance to Border Staff to reinforce knowledge of these procedures.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-10-23T16:28:51.6644356Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92250/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92250/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92250/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-26","Immigration Controls: Infectious Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions officials in his Department have had with their counterparts in the Home Department about steps to identify and segregate travellers entering the UK who may be carrying a virulent communicable disease.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","209703"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92251","Department of Health","false","2014-10-15","<p>Public Health England and its predecessors have monitored the United Kingdom’s human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) epidemic since the early 1980s.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The following table summarises the number newly diagnosed with HIV, the number of deaths occurring among people with HIV, the number of people accessing HIV care (i.e. diagnosed prevalent HIV infections) in the UK from 1985-2012, and the number of death certificates that specifically mention ‘HIV’, ‘Human Immunodeficiency Virus’, ‘AIDS’ or ‘Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome’.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Annual number of new HIV diagnoses, UK</p></td><td><p>Annual number of deaths among people with HIV, UK</p></td><td><p>Number living with diagnosed HIV* at year end, UK</p></td><td><p>Number of Deaths with HIV/AIDS listed on the death certificate, UK</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1985</p></td><td><p>2,938</p></td><td><p>153</p></td><td><p>3,635</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1986</p></td><td><p>2,648</p></td><td><p>332</p></td><td><p>5,955</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1987</p></td><td><p>2,385</p></td><td><p>425</p></td><td><p>7,917</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1988</p></td><td><p>1,940</p></td><td><p>514</p></td><td><p>9,345</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1989</p></td><td><p>2,169</p></td><td><p>779</p></td><td><p>10,739</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1990</p></td><td><p>2,571</p></td><td><p>943</p></td><td><p>12,376</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1991</p></td><td><p>2,847</p></td><td><p>1,150</p></td><td><p>14,077</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1992</p></td><td><p>2,922</p></td><td><p>1,267</p></td><td><p>15,745</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1993</p></td><td><p>2,835</p></td><td><p>1,575</p></td><td><p>17,014</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1994</p></td><td><p>2,824</p></td><td><p>1,732</p></td><td><p>18,124</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1995</p></td><td><p>2,931</p></td><td><p>1,731</p></td><td><p>13,817</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1996</p></td><td><p>2,903</p></td><td><p>1,480</p></td><td><p>13,947</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1997</p></td><td><p>2,865</p></td><td><p>748</p></td><td><p>15,074</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1998</p></td><td><p>2,915</p></td><td><p>513</p></td><td><p>16,831</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1999</p></td><td><p>3,267</p></td><td><p>470</p></td><td><p>20,012</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2000</p></td><td><p>3,962</p></td><td><p>485</p></td><td><p>22,508</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2001</p></td><td><p>5,139</p></td><td><p>478</p></td><td><p>25,994</p></td><td><p>17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2002</p></td><td><p>6,395</p></td><td><p>523</p></td><td><p>30,849</p></td><td><p>46</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2003</p></td><td><p>7,409</p></td><td><p>564</p></td><td><p>35,971</p></td><td><p>112</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2004</p></td><td><p>7,786</p></td><td><p>488</p></td><td><p>41,168</p></td><td><p>178</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2005</p></td><td><p>7,928</p></td><td><p>588</p></td><td><p>46,527</p></td><td><p>258</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2006</p></td><td><p>7,498</p></td><td><p>563</p></td><td><p>51,535</p></td><td><p>274</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007</p></td><td><p>7,388</p></td><td><p>596</p></td><td><p>56,211</p></td><td><p>304</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>7,273</p></td><td><p>610</p></td><td><p>61,019</p></td><td><p>293</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>6,676</p></td><td><p>589</p></td><td><p>65,213</p></td><td><p>297</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>6,362</p></td><td><p>705</p></td><td><p>69,298</p></td><td><p>318</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>6,219</p></td><td><p>538</p></td><td><p>73,645</p></td><td><p>231</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>6,364</p></td><td><p>488</p></td><td><p>77,614</p></td><td><p>286</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>* Numbers of people accessing HIV care in the UK before 2000 were estimated.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><em>Notes:</em></p><p> </p><ol start="1" type="I"><li>As not all people infected with HIV die of the condition this is not necessarily recorded on death certificates, it is also known that there was under reporting on death certificates in the early years of the epidemic.</li><li>New cases of HIV diagnoses are reported centrally from clinicians and laboratories.</li><li>Death reports are collated from clinicians and supplemented with reports from the Office for National Statistics. Deaths include HIV and non-HIV related mortality.</li><li>Patients diagnosed with HIV are seen for care and treatment at a network of free accessible HIV outpatient services. Access to, and retention in, HIV is extremely high; consequently these data correspond to diagnosed prevalence. The number of patients newly diagnosed and the number of deaths each year will not directly correspond to diagnosed prevalence; this is due to migration patterns and a small subset of patients (&lt;3%) who do not attend care after diagnosis.</li></ol><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","209702","2014-10-15T16:24:43.8270315Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92251/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92251/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92251/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-26","HIV Infection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will place in the Library data on (a) the number of people diagnosed with HIV, (b) the number of HIV deaths and (c) HIV prevalence in England since 1985.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","209726"
