how many officials in her Department of what (a) gender, (b) ethnicity and (c) age received the Civil Service Employment Policy Performance Management System's (i) exceeded, (ii) met and (iii) must improve performance mark in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","209486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92278","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-15","<p>In the coming months DFID will hold consultations to inform the direction and choices for the future of strategic financing to civil society.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-10-15T15:38:38.0117879Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92278/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92278/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92278/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-09-26","Developing Countries: Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, when she plans to announce future programme partnership funding from her Department from 2015-16 onwards.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","209786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92279","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-15","<p>The Department for International Development is delivering £23 million in response to the crisis in Iraq. Our Advisors on the ground are working closely with aid agencies, the UN and the Kurdistan Regional Government to further assess humanitarian needs. The UK government is lobbying the UN and the Government of Iraq to meet the humanitarian needs of all Iraq’s citizens, to protect minorities and to improve the tracking and reporting of human rights abuses including crimes of sexual and gender based violence.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Jointly with the FCO we are looking at how UK expertise could support the new Iraqi government build a stable and prosperous country.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-10-15T15:40:05.7189166Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92279/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92279/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92279/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-09-26","Iraq","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what plans her Department has to (a) increase humanitarian aid and (b) provide development assistance for state building in Iraq; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","209747"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92280","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-15","<p>DFID has not received any reports of any impact on UK aid operations inside Syria resulting from UK military action in Iraq. We continue to closely monitor the situation with our partners on the ground, and to receive regular reports from them.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-10-15T15:39:22.1372707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92280/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92280/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92280/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-09-26","Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the implications of UK military action in Iraq for UK humanitarian aid to the victims of the conflict in Syria; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","209748"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92281","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-15","<p>DFID’s primary purpose is poverty reduction. We have a comprehensive portfolio of governance and social development programmes in Africa and Asia. Our development programmes broadly contribute to tackling violent extremism by helping build better states and societies that can respond more effectively.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-10-15T15:44:37.7813582Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92281/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92281/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92281/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-09-26","Radicalism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what new initiatives her Department plans to take in partnership with the governments of countries in Africa and Asia to combat Islamist extremism.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Bayley","York Central","Hugh Bayley","209749"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92282","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-16","<p>A 2012 nutrition survey of mothers and children under 5 conducted by Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (DPRK) authorities (with support from the Word Food Programme (WFP), UNICEF and the World Health Organisation) showed that average nutrition levels were improved from a 2009 survey, but that in some provinces stunting rates remained above acceptable levels. A joint Food and Agriculture Organisation (FAO) and (WFP) Crop and Food Security Assessment in 2013 estimated an improved aggregate food security situation for the marketing year 2013/14, but noted that the household food security levels and lack of diet diversity continued to pose a threat to the most vulnerable children, elderly, sick and pregnant and breastfeeding women.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2014-10-16T16:52:37.6797253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92282/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92282/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92282/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-09-26","North Korea","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the effect of persistent malnutrition on the population of the Democratic People's Republic of North Korea; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","209690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92283","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-15","<p>CDC requires all of its fund managers and investee companies to apply and demonstrate progress towards the ILO core labour standards, including specifically ILO Convention 111 on Discrimination (Employment and Occupation). CDC investment policy states that non-discrimination (including disability) is a requirement for all investee companies.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-10-15T15:40:50.8691345Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92283/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92283/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92283/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-09-26","CDC","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will review CDC investment policy to determine if the requirement that investee companies have non-discrimination policies in place effectively addresses the inclusion of disabled people as employees, customers and service users.","false","Biography information for Mr Mark Williams","Ceredigion","Mr Mark Williams","209700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92284","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-15","<p>Operation Patwin was the armed forces contribution to the UK Government’s humanitarian response to Typhoon Haiyan in the Philippines. Supporting the Department for International Development (DFID), the armed forces delivered essential supplies to an estimated 47,000 people and provided logistical support. The marginal cost to the MOD amounted to £8,950,281. This sum was reimbursed by DFID under the terms of a memorandum of understanding covering military support to humanitarian assistance missions. DFID has commissioned an independent evaluation of its Typhoon Haiyan response, and plans to share the findings with partners early in 2015.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2014-10-15T16:36:55.2225716Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92284/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92284/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92284/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-09-26","Philippines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many people were assisted by Operation Patwin; what costs were incurred by her Department in supporting Operation Patwin, by category of expenditure; and if she will publish her Department's learning review of that operation.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Gavin Shuker","209715"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92285","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-10-15","<p>HM Courts &amp; Tribunal Service does not collate the information requested. This information could only be provided at a disproportionate cost by manually checking individual tribunal files.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-10-15T16:11:29.6758924Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92285/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92285/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92285/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-09-26","Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many companies have been successfully taken to tribunal by employees for not complying with minimum wage legislation in each of the last nine years.","false","Biography information for Margot James","Stourbridge","Margot James","209707"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92286","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-10-15","<p>The Justice Secretary has not met with any children’s privacy campaigners in the past 12 months.</p>","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Simon Hughes",,"2014-10-15T10:04:39.1806789Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92286/answer","Biography information for Simon Hughes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92286/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92286/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-09-26","Children: Privacy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what meetings he has had with children's privacy campaigners in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","209798"
