"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92321","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-14","The Department’s target is to transfer 1873 records to The National Archives (TNA) by 31 December 2014. On current plans these will be transferred by the end of October 2014. After that date no files will be outstanding. There are five staff engaged in reviewing records for transfer to TNA.","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-10-14T10:04:01.8842597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92321/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92321/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92321/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-26","Public Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what targets have been set for the release of his Department's material to the National Archives; what progress has been made in meeting those targets; and how many staff in his Department are engaged in reviewing records for that purpose.","false","Biography information for Lord Beith","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Sir Alan Beith","209619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92322","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-14","<p>The Department has no plans to review the way the Shared Accommodation Rates are calculated. The Rent Officer Services set the rates in line with the current DWP policy for uprating Local Housing Allowance and with reference to evidence of achieved rents in the local area.</p><p> </p><p>In 2014/15, 56 out of the 192 Shared Accommodation Rates have been increased by 4%, in those areas where there is the greatest divergence between LHA rates and local rents.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-10-14T10:42:30.9331163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92322/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92322/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92322/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-26","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will commission a review and recalculation of the shared accommodation rate to ensure that it reflects the real cost of rooms in shared houses.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","209552"
