"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91695","Cabinet Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>Further to the answer the Member for Braintree gave on 5 September 2014 to Question <a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmhansrd/cm140905/text/140905w0001.htm#14090533001726" target="_blank">UIN207293,207294,207295,207323,207324 </a></p><p>Society Network Foundation’s accounts for 2012-13 were published in Jan 2014 and reviewed by Social Investment Business as part of standard grant monitoring. These accounts showed that funds had been transferred from the Get In grant to cover a deficit in unrestricted funds. Further information and explanation was requested at this time and discussed with Society Network Foundation. As a result, a request for £33,994 to be returned was issued to Society Network Foundation on the 9th of May 2014.</p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","209174 ; 209175 ; 209178 ; 209215","2014-10-13T15:59:52.1831492Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91695/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91695/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91695/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-09-12","Big Society Network","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether Ministers in his Department instructed special advisers to ask NESTA or BIG Lottery to fund the Big Society Network or the Social Network Foundation.","false","Biography information for Lisa Nandy","Wigan","Lisa Nandy","209176"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91696","HM Treasury","false","2014-10-17","<p>The Government takes the enforcement of the National Minimum Wage (NMW) very seriously. HMRC review every complaint that is referred to them by the Pay and Work Rights Helpline. In addition, by collating and analysing data received from various sources, HMRC ensure targeted enforcement to identify employers across the United Kingdom who are more likely to be not paying NMW.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government has increased the financial penalty percentage from 50% to 100% of the unpaid wages owed to workers, and the maximum penalty from £5,000 to £20,000. These new limits are now in force where arrears are identified in pay reference periods on or after 7 March 2014. The Government will also bring in primary legislation as soon as possible so that the maximum £20,000 penalty can apply to each underpaid worker.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The following table shows the number of employers in the home care sector over the past four years where HMRC have commenced and completed investigations. It also shows the percentage of instances where employers were found to be non-complaint with NMW legislation as a result of these investigations. <ins></ins></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Investigations</p></td><td> </td><td><p>Percentage</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>13</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>23%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>46</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>39%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>24</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>46%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>13</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>15%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-10-17T13:16:28.927541Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91696/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91696/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91696/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-12","Home Care Services: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many home care providers were investigated by HM Revenue and Customs in each of the last four years; and what proportion of those providers was found not to be paying the national minimum wage.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","209191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91697","HM Treasury","false","2014-10-13","<p>A Member State should exchange information about a tax agreement it has made with an international company when the Member State considers that the tax agreement may result in a loss of tax in another Member State.</p><p> </p><p>This requirement is set out in the EU Council Directive 2011/16/EU on administrative cooperation in the field of taxation.</p><p> </p><p>There is no legal basis to exchange information where a Member State reaches a legal agreement with an international company on a purely domestic matter that could never directly affect the tax base of another Member State.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-10-13T15:05:55.9736508Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91697/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91697/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91697/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-12","Multinational Companies: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what requirement there is for EU member states to exchange information on tax agreements between them and international companies.","false","Biography information for Austin Mitchell","Great Grimsby","Austin Mitchell","209221"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91698","HM Treasury","false","2014-10-13","<p>HM Revenue &amp; Customs (HMRC) published its Digital Strategy in December 2012 to deliver a transparent tax system enabled by customer-focused digital services which are straightforward and convenient to use.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC have subsequently begun to transform its products and services as part of the Government’s digital by default agenda.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC is doing this through the development of Digital Exemplar services such as for Self Assessment and Pay As You Earn and recently the Tax Credits online renewal service which enabled more than 400,000 customers to renew their tax credits online this year.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-10-13T15:07:02.4838037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91698/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91698/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91698/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-12","Revenue and Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps HM Revenue and Customs has taken to improve online customer service in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Paul Uppal","Wolverhampton South West","Paul Uppal","209234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91699","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-01-19","<p>We have invested more than £2 billion to enable council and housing association homes to be brought up to the Decent Homes standard, and have announced a £150 million funding pot to enable the regeneration of some of our most run-down estates.</p><p> </p><p>Reforms we have introduced have given councils greater freedoms, including the retention of their full rental income. All 167 council landlords in England now have a long-term, stable source of funding, which they can use to better meet the needs of their tenants and local area, and have, on average, 15% more to spend on managing and maintaining their homes than under the previous system.</p><p> </p><p>While we recognise that transformational estate regeneration may require some demolition of existing homes, this will need to be clearly justified. We would expect landlords to first consider options to upgrade and refurbish existing homes, in consultation with residents, in line with George Clarke’s 12 point plan (<a href="http://georgeclarke.com/2012/11/george-clarkes-empty-homes-manifesto-delivered-to-government-today/" target="_blank">http://georgeclarke.com/2012/11/george-clarkes-empty-homes-manifesto-delivered-to-government-today/</a>).</p><p> </p><p>It is of course important that any modernisation, regeneration or demolition takes place only once the views of the local community have been taken into account.</p><p> </p><p>I also refer the hon. Member to the Written Ministerial Statement of 16 January 2015, <em>Official Report</em>, Column 35-37WS, which outlines what this Government has done to promote refurbishment and getting empty building back into use.</p><p><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmhansrd/cm150116/wmstext/150116m0001.htm#15011650000003" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmhansrd/cm150116/wmstext/150116m0001.htm#15011650000003</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-01-19T16:21:13.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91699/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91699/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91699/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-09-12","High Rise Flats","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what support is available to councils and housing associations to (a) modernise and (b) demolish tower blocks; and what guidance his Department provides to local authorities on tower blocks.","false","Biography information for Austin Mitchell","Great Grimsby","Austin Mitchell","209196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91700","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-10-21","<p>Although the Ministry of Justice has responsibility for cremation legislation and policy, it does not have operational responsibility for cremations and so does not hold the requested information. The costs involved to obtain the information would be disproportionate.</p>","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Simon Hughes",,"2014-10-21T16:20:53.0191893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91700/answer","Biography information for Simon Hughes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91700/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91700/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-09-12","Cremation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many unclaimed funeral urns containing human ashes there are at each council owned crematorium in England.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mark Hendrick","209162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91701","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-10-13","<p>In 2012, Sport England invested £134,620 of National Lottery funding into UK Deaf Sport to support the UK team attend the Deaflympics at Sofia in 2013. No lottery funding has been allocated to Deaflympics by UK Sport. £75,000 of Exchequer funding was provided by UK Sport to support Deaflympics 2005.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-10-13T13:37:11.9123795Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91701/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91701/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91701/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-09-12","Deaflympics: National Lottery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much lottery funding has been allocated to the Deaflympics programme in each year since 1997.","false","Biography information for Stephen Lloyd","Eastbourne","Stephen Lloyd","209156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91702","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-10-13","<p>Team GB won 65 Olympic medals and Paralympics GB won 120 Paralympic medals at London 2012. The investment for that cycle can be found on UK Sport’s website here: <a href="http://www.uksport.gov.uk/sport/summer/" target="_blank">http://www.uksport.gov.uk/sport/summer/</a></p><p> </p><p>Team GB won four Olympic medals and Paralympics GB won six Paralympic medals at Sochi 2014. The investment for that cycle can be found on UK Sport’s website here: <a href="http://www.uksport.gov.uk/sport/winter/" target="_blank">http://www.uksport.gov.uk/sport/winter/</a></p><p> </p><p>In 2012, Sport England invested £134,620 of National Lottery funding into UK Deaf Sport to support the UK team attend the Deaflympics at Sofia in 2013. At the games, the GB team won two silver and three bronze medals.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-10-13T13:38:33.3451666Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91702/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91702/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91702/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-09-12","Sports: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the total investment was for each podium place won by the GB (a) Olympic Team, (b) Paralympic Team and (c) Deaflympics Team in the most recent games in which each team competed.","false","Biography information for Stephen Lloyd","Eastbourne","Stephen Lloyd","209157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91703","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-10-13","<p>UK Deaf Sport is one of seven national disability sport organisations Sport England is working closely with to get more disabled people playing sport. Sport England has invested £281,974 into UK Deaf Sport to provide disability and impairment expertise to create more opportunities for deaf people to play sport regularly. This is part of Sport England’s £171 million investment into disability sport.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-10-13T13:37:47.1937641Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91703/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91703/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91703/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-09-12","Sports: Hearing Impaired","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps his Department is taking to raise the profile of deaf sport.","false","Biography information for Stephen Lloyd","Eastbourne","Stephen Lloyd","209158"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91704","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-13","<p>As part of Army 2020, 7,280 soldiers were made redundant in tranches 1 to 3 of the Armed Forces Redundancy Programme, and around 1,000 personnel were selected in the fourth and final tranche, the majority of whom will have left the Army by June 2015. All personnel selected receive at least six months notice, twelve if they did not apply for redundancy.<br><br>Eligibility for Single Service Living Accommodation ceases when an individual leaves the Army. As part of the redundancy process all individuals are provided with advice on housing after leaving the Armed Forces. This includes the issue, on request, of a cessation certificate up to six months before eligibility ends. This allows individuals to request assistance with housing options from Councils and Housing Associations.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-13T16:48:59.2664358Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91704/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91704/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91704/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91704/answer/previousversion/21608","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-12","Armed Forces: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many soldiers made redundant as a result of Army 2020 have been evicted from army barracks; and how much notice those soldiers were given before eviction.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","209209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91705","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-24","<p>Israel is an important strategic partner of the UK and, as part of that relationship, the Ministry of Defence has an ongoing and wide ranging dialogue with the Israeli Defence Force and Israeli Ministry of Defence. This engagement is in line with the Government's policy of supporting the Middle East peace process by having a balanced relationship with the Israelis and the Palestinians. Due to the widespread nature of our engagement with Israel throughout the Services the requested information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","209226","2014-11-24T16:53:32.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91705/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91705/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91705/answer","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91705/answer/previousversion/22738","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-12","Israel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Israeli Defence Force officers have visited UK defence establishments since 1 July 2014; and what the purpose of each such visit was.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Corbyn","Islington North","Jeremy Corbyn","209218"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91706","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-24","<p>Israel is an important strategic partner of the UK and, as part of that relationship, the Ministry of Defence has an ongoing and wide ranging dialogue with the Israeli Defence Force and Israeli Ministry of Defence. This engagement is in line with the Government's policy of supporting the Middle East peace process by having a balanced relationship with the Israelis and the Palestinians. Due to the widespread nature of our engagement with Israel throughout the Services the requested information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","209218","2014-11-24T16:53:32.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91706/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91706/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91706/answer","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91706/answer/previousversion/22741","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-12","Israel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many UK military personnel have had official meetings with the Israeli Defence Force since 1 July 2014; and what the purpose of each such meeting was.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Corbyn","Islington North","Jeremy Corbyn","209226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91707","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-10","<p>The private and state schools which have a Combined Cadet Force (CCF) unit are shown on the attached list. Of the state schools, 41 are schools which have established CCF units under the Cadet Expansion Programme.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-11-10T17:55:05.3858493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91707/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91707/answer","209251 Private and State Schools with a Combined Cadet Force].doc","209251 Private and State Schools with a Combined Cadet Force].doc","209251-Combined Cadet Force Private/State Schools","209251-Combined Cadet Force Private/State Schools","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91707/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91707/answer/previousversion/22790","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-12","Combined Cadet Force","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which (a) private and (b) state schools have a Combined Cadet Force unit.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","209251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91708","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-16","<p>There are currently 388 Sea Cadet Units across the UK. I will place details of these locations in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-16T16:09:48.6543415Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91708/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91708/answer","PQO5153.doc","PQO5153.doc","Sea Cadet units across the UK","Sea Cadet units across the UK","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91708/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-12","Sea Cadet Corps","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will list all Sea Cadets units.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","209256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91709","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-15","<p>This information is not routinely recorded, however, between 2011 and 2014, on average, 24% of respondents (Officers and Other Ranks) to the Armed Forces Continuous Attitude Survey stated that they had previous service in the Sea Cadets, Army Cadet Force or Air Training Corps. Over the same period an average of 20% of Officer respondents stated that they had previous service in the Combined Cadet Force.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-15T15:06:52.452992Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91709/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91709/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91709/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-12","Armed Forces: Cadets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many former members of the (a) Sea Cadets, (b) Army Cadet Force, (c) Air Training Corps and (d) Combined Cadet Force subsequently joined the armed forces in financial years 2005-06 and 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","209254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91710","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-16","<p>There are currently 952 Air Training Corps Squadrons in operation. A copy of this list will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-16T16:08:03.6061674Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91710/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91710/answer","Copy of 20140929-PQ-05157-Sir-Nicholas-Soames-MP-ATC_Units[1].pdf","Copy of 20140929-PQ-05157-Sir-Nicholas-Soames-MP-ATC_Units[1].pdf","Air Training Corps Squadrons in operation.","Air Training Corps Squadrons in operation.","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91710/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-12","Air Training Corps","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what Air Training Corps squadrons are in operation.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","209255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91711","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-16","<p>As at 1 September 2014 there were 1,946 Army Cadet Force Detachments across the UK, and 242 Combined Cadet Forces Army contingents.<br><br>I will place details of these detachments and contingents in the Library of the House.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-16T16:09:03.9390253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91711/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91711/answer","Number of ACF Detachments - CCF (Army) Contingents.xls","Number of ACF Detachments - CCF (Army) Contingents.xls","Detachments and contingents List","Detachments and contingents List","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91711/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-12","Army Cadet Force","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what Army Cadet Force detachments are in operation.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","209258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91712","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-16","<p>This information is not held, however, the 2011 Defence Youth Engagement Review estimated the cost of Cadet Forces in financial year 2009-10 to be £154.4 million. Of this total, the breakdown was as follows:</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td>Sea Cadet Corps</td><td>Army Cadet Force</td><td>Air Training Corps</td><td>Combined Cadet Force</td></tr><tr><td>£11.3 million</td><td>£80.4 million</td><td>£36.7 million</td><td>£26 million</td></tr></tbody></table>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-16T15:02:21.2358331Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91712/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91712/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91712/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-09-12","Armed Forces: Cadets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department spent on (a) Sea Cadets, (b) Army Cadet Force, (c) Air Training Corps and (d) Combined Cadet Force in the financial years 2005-06 to 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","209259"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91713","Department for Education","false","2014-10-13","<p>No. An independent public inquiry would not be appropriate while a related police investigation is ongoing.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-10-13T15:27:04.2081471Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91713/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91713/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91713/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-09-12","Kings Free Schools and Academies Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will call an independent public inquiry into events at Kings Free Schools and Academies Trust.","false","Biography information for Mr David Ward","Bradford East","Mr David Ward","209208"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91714","Department for Education","false","2014-10-13","<p>The estimated cost of advertising for initial teacher training courses for each financial year since 2010 is:</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>2010-11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013-14</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Estimate of advertising costs</p></td><td><p>£3,530,000</p></td><td><p>£2,480,000</p></td><td><p>£4,650,000</p></td><td><p>£1,480,000</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>These estimates include purchased media space in TV, newspapers, magazines, posters and online.</p><p> </p><p>The changes in expenditure over this period reflect the change in delivery of advertising, which emphasises digital and social media marketing, and other promotional activity over television and press advertising.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-10-13T10:13:19.3528961Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91714/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91714/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91714/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-09-12","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate she has made of the cost of advertising for initial teaching training courses in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","209179"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91715","Department for Education","false","2014-10-13","<p>The proportion of 16-, 17- and 18-year-olds in employment but not in education or training at the end of each year since 1994 is available in Table 5a of the ‘Main SFR tables and figures’ spreadsheet. This is part of the “Participation in education, training and employment, age 16 to 18” statistical first release, which is published online at:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/participation-in-education-training-and-employment-age-16-to-18" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistics/participation-in-education-training-and-employment-age-16-to-18</a></p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2014-10-13T13:17:40.6943844Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91715/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91715/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91715/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-09-12","Employment: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate her Department has made of the proportion of young people aged (a) 16, (b) 17 and (c) 18 who have been recorded as being in jobs without training in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Rushanara Ali","Bethnal Green and Bow","Rushanara Ali","209172"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91716","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-10-13","<p>In Bonn, our departmental negotiators will be working towards a successful outcome at the Lima COP in December this year, where we want to: i) pave the way for countries to bring forward their post-2020 emissions reduction offers for the new agreement in early 2015, ii) agree the elements of the draft negotiating text for Paris, and iii) agree on the next steps on enhanced action to close the pre-2020 mitigation gap.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-10-13T12:54:57.5286344Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91716/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91716/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91716/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-09-12","Climate Change: International Cooperation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what proposals he plans to make at the Ad Hoc Working Group on the Durban Platform for Enhanced Action (ADP) second session sixth part in Bonn in October 2014.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","209198"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91717","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-10-13","<p>The 2014-15 budget for the Office of Unconventional Gas and Oil is currently £1.8m, which covers an office of 15 staff as well as programme funding for activities including research, communications and public engagement .</p><p>Current plans for 15-16 are for £1.8m, but are subject to DECC’s internal business planning process. Future years will be subject to Spending Review discussions with the Treasury on DECC’s overall baseline.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-10-13T12:54:15.0604621Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91717/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91717/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91717/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-09-12","Office of Unconventional Gas and Oil","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what the budget is for the Office of Unconventional Gas and Oil for each of the years 2014-15 to 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mark Hendrick","209161"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91718","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-10-13","<p>The table below shows the number of hydroelectric schemes in the High Peak, England and UK, as at the end of 2012. Data as at the end of 2013 will be available on 25 September 2014. DECC does not distinguish between small and micro-scale hydro-electricity.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><em>High Peak</em></p></td><td><p><em>England</em></p></td><td><p><em>UK</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong><em>Large-scale (&gt;5 MW)</em></strong></p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>55</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong><em>Small-scale (&gt;= 5 MW)</em></strong></p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>205</p></td><td><p>614</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>England and UK total hydro figures in <em>Renewable electricity in Scotland, Wales, Northern Ireland and the regions of England in 2012</em>, Energy Trends September 2013, available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/energy-trends-september-2013-special-feature-articles-renewable-electricity-in-scotland-wales-northern-ireland-and-the-regions-of-england-in-201" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/energy-trends-september-2013-special-feature-articles-renewable-electricity-in-scotland-wales-northern-ireland-and-the-regions-of-england-in-201</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-10-13T12:55:55.9142025Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91718/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91718/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91718/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-09-12","Hydroelectric Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many (a) large scale, (b) small scale and (c) micro-scale hydroelectric schemes are in operation in (i) the High Peak, (ii) England and (iii) the UK.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bingham","High Peak","Andrew Bingham","209194"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91719","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-10-13","<p>Seafood manufacturers are precluded from applying for regional structural aid through the provisions set out in the European Commission’s state aid rules for the fisheries sector which apply to businesses involved in the processing of fish and fisheries products, as well as to the catching sector. The Commission views this as necessary to avoid distortion of the market and to ensure consistency with the objectives of the European Union’s Common Fisheries Policy. However, support is available to small and medium-sized seafood manufacturers via the European Fisheries Fund, and its successor, the European Maritime and Fisheries Fund.</p><p>Any application for alternative funding would need to be considered on a case-by-case basis subject to the specific request.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-10-13T16:19:26.9764153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91719/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91719/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91719/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-09-12","Fisheries: EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, for what reason seafood manufacturers are precluded from applying for regional structural aid; and for what alternative funding they can apply.","false","Biography information for Austin Mitchell","Great Grimsby","Austin Mitchell","209181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91720","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-10-13","<p>At the end of 2014 Q1, hydro-electricity represented 8.2 per cent of UK renewable electricity capacity, and 1.8 per cent of all generating capacity.</p><p><em>Source:</em></p><p><em>Hydro and renewable electricity capacity from table ET 6.1, available at:</em></p><p><em><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/energy-trends-section-6-renewables" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/energy-trends-section-6-renewables</a></em></p><p><em>Total generating capacity (end-2012) from table DUKES 5.12, available at:</em></p><p><em><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/electricity-chapter-5-digest-of-united-kingdom-energy-statistics-dukes" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/electricity-chapter-5-digest-of-united-kingdom-energy-statistics-dukes</a></em></p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-10-13T12:56:54.3649791Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91720/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91720/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91720/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-09-12","Hydroelectric Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what proportion of the UK's (a) total and (b) renewable energy generating capacity is provided by hydroelectric power stations.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bingham","High Peak","Andrew Bingham","209201"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91721","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-10-13","<p>There have been no discussions with the Dutch government about its planned incineration tax.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-10-13T16:11:24.2245661Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91721/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91721/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91721/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-09-12","Incinerators: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent discussions she has had with the Dutch government about its planned incineration tax.","true","Biography information for Dame Caroline Spelman","Meriden","Mrs Caroline Spelman","209192"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91722","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-10-13","<p>Following the horsemeat fraud incident the Government commissioned Professor Chris Elliott, of Queen’s University Belfast, to carry out an independent review into the Integrity and Assurance of Food Supply Networks. This was not an inquiry into the horsemeat fraud itself but a much wider review of the issues which impact on consumer confidence in the authenticity of their food.</p><p>Professor Elliott’s Review was published on 4 September 2014 and sets out a systems approach to improve the food supply chain. The integrity of our food and empowering consumers to make informed choices are central to this Government’s vision of a competitive, resilient and growing UK food and farming sector. This is an important issue and it is only right that upon her appointment on 15 July 2014 the Secretary of State gave Professor Elliott’s final report the time and consideration it deserved before its publication. The report was published when Parliament returned after recess.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-10-13T16:16:07.2234603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91722/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91722/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91722/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-09-12","Horse Meat","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when the Government plans to publish the report of the inquiry into the wrongful selling of horsemeat; and what the reasons are for the time taken to publish that report.","false","Biography information for Austin Mitchell","Great Grimsby","Austin Mitchell","209182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91723","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-10-13","<p>The UK secured a landing obligation as part of the reformed Common Fisheries Policy which entered into force on the 1 January 2014. The landing obligation comes into force in a phased timetable starting with pelagic fisheries on 1 January 2015 and extending to other fisheries from 2016.</p><p>Detailed preparatory work is underway with the fishing industry, European Union Member States and other stakeholders about how we can best implement these changes in practice. This includes supporting the industry in reducing discards ahead of the discard ban coming into effect, including through our successful catch quota scheme.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-10-13T16:22:46.8203103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91723/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91723/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91723/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-09-12","Fishing Catches","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans she has for implementation of the EU ban on fish discards; and what representations she has received on the sale or disposal of fish discarded before that ban comes into effect.","false","Biography information for Austin Mitchell","Great Grimsby","Austin Mitchell","209183"
